---
import Layout from "@/layouts/Layout.astro";
import { Nav } from "@/components/landing/Nav";
import { Footer } from "@/components/landing/Footer";

const LAST_UPDATED = "July 4, 2026";
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy - Loopress WordPress Developer Tools"
  description="Read the Loopress privacy policy to understand how we collect, use, and protect your personal data as a user of our WordPress developer tools."
  canonical="https://loopress.dev/privacy"
>
  <div class="min-h-screen bg-background text-foreground">
    <Nav client:load />
    <main class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-24">
      <h1 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-muted-foreground">Last updated: {LAST_UPDATED}</p>

      <p class="mt-6 text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">
        Loopress ("we", "us") is currently in beta. This policy describes the data we
        collect today, at this stage of the product, and will be updated as new features (paid
        plans, team accounts) ship. Questions? <a href="/contact" class="underline underline-offset-2 hover:text-foreground">Contact us</a>.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-10 space-y-10 text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-base font-medium text-foreground">What we collect</h2>
          <ul class="mt-3 list-disc space-y-2 pl-5">
            <li>
              <strong class="text-foreground/90">Beta waitlist:</strong> if you leave your email to join the beta,
              we store it with our email provider (Brevo) to notify you about product updates.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong class="text-foreground/90">Contact form:</strong> name, email, subject, and message, sent to
              our team and used only to reply to your request.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong class="text-foreground/90">Loopress account:</strong> if you sign in to the Loopress console
              with Google, we store your email address and a Google account identifier. We do not
              request or store your Google password.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong class="text-foreground/90">CLI usage:</strong> the CLI and WordPress plugin run against your
              own WordPress site. Nothing is sent to Loopress unless you run <code class="rounded bg-card px-1 py-0.5 font-mono text-xs">lps login</code>
              to connect a project to your account, in which case project metadata and WordPress
              credentials (encrypted at rest) are synced so CI deployments don't need separate secrets.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong class="text-foreground/90">Website analytics:</strong> we use Vercel Analytics, which does not
              use cookies and reports aggregated, non-identifying traffic data.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-base font-medium text-foreground">How we use it</h2>
          <p class="mt-3">
            To operate the service, respond to your messages, send product updates you've opted
            into, and understand how the site is used so we can improve it. We do not sell your
            data, and we do not share it with third parties for their own marketing purposes.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-base font-medium text-foreground">Third-party services</h2>
          <p class="mt-3">
            We rely on a small number of providers to run Loopress: <strong class="text-foreground/90">Brevo</strong> (email
            and contact form delivery), <strong class="text-foreground/90">Google</strong> (sign-in), <strong class="text-foreground/90">Vercel</strong> (hosting
            and analytics), and <strong class="text-foreground/90">GitHub</strong> (distribution of the open-source CLI and
            plugin). Each processes data under its own privacy policy.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-base font-medium text-foreground">Data retention</h2>
          <p class="mt-3">
            We keep account and contact data for as long as your account is active, or as needed
            to respond to your request. You can ask us to delete your data at any time via the
            <a href="/contact" class="underline underline-offset-2 hover:text-foreground">contact page</a>.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-base font-medium text-foreground">Your rights</h2>
          <p class="mt-3">
            Depending on where you live, you may have the right to access, correct, export, or
            delete your personal data. Reach out via the <a href="/contact" class="underline underline-offset-2 hover:text-foreground">contact page</a>
            and we'll act on it.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-base font-medium text-foreground">Cookies &amp; local storage</h2>
          <p class="mt-3">
            The website does not use tracking or advertising cookies. It stores a single local
            storage entry on your device to remember your light/dark theme preference.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-base font-medium text-foreground">Children</h2>
          <p class="mt-3">
            Loopress is a developer tool and is not directed at, or knowingly used to collect data
            from, children under 16.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-base font-medium text-foreground">Changes to this policy</h2>
          <p class="mt-3">
            As Loopress moves out of beta and adds paid plans and team features, this policy will
            be updated to reflect what's actually collected. We'll update the date at the top when
            that happens.
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </main>
    <Footer />
  </div>
</Layout>
